text: Alanna Noel Ubach (born October 3, 1975) is an actress, vocal artist and singer of Mexican, Puerto Rican, and Spanish descent. She is known for her roles in Coco as Mama Imelda, Legally Blonde as Serena McGuire, Meet the Fockers as Isabel Villalobos. She played Jeanine Pirro in the 2019 movie Bombshell and Suze Howard in the HBO series Euphoria.
